SUMMARY:A License to Chill at the Penngrove Pub
DESCRIPTION:A Jimmy Buffet tribute + more! \nBAND BIO: \nTom Birch \nFounder and lead singer. Tom is a prolific song writer and penned the words and music for the groups 2020 album release “Full Speed Ahead” available on iTunes\, Spotify\, etc. Tom’s musicianship dates back to 1970 playing in\, with\, and for many local Bay Area bands. “I enjoy getting our audiences involved with the music\, dancing\, singing \nRobert Clot \nRobert started playing guitar at age of eight. His first stage appearance was in the 4th grade playing Venture songs at his grammar school. Being in a band has been part of his life like riding a bicycle. \nPedal Steel caught his ear in his teens\, listening to country music found on the AM radio. \nHe started playing in clubs at age of 19. \nBrad Smith \nBrad’s been playing the piano since he was 7 years old – when his parents forced him into lessons (he’s very grateful now!). He co-wrote and recorded an album in high school\, and in college he built a business playing wedding ceremonies on the keys and DJing the dance floor after. He’s had the privilege of teaching piano to a dozen or so
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/a-license-to-chill-at-the-penngrove-pub/
LOCATION:Penngrove Pub\, 10005 Main Street\, Penngrove\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
GEO:38.297140;-122.666400
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=Penngrove Pub 10005 Main Street Penngrove CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=10005 Main Street:geo:-122.666400,38.297140
END:VEVENT
