SUMMARY:Sunday Funday SUP Paddle on the Petaluma River
DESCRIPTION:Ease into your Sunday with a relaxed guided paddle on the beautiful Petaluma River—Petaluma’s “Longest Park.” \nJoin The Floathouse crew from 9:45–11:15 AM for a friendly\, social stand-up paddle in the calm\, protected waters of the Petaluma River. It’s a great way to spend time outdoors\, enjoy the river’s natural beauty\, and connect with fellow community members while experiencing Sonoma County from the water. \nYou’ll paddle on stable TAO Fit boards\, with Floathouse staff along to guide the outing and keep the group moving comfortably along the river. This paddle is best suited for people who have been on a board before and are ready to enjoy a relaxed\, easygoing outing—no lesson required. \nThe Floathouse is located right in the heart of vibrant downtown Petaluma\, so when the paddle wraps up you’re just steps away from some of the area’s best coffee\, pastries\, brunch spots\, and local shops. Make a Sunday Funday paddle part of your weekend ritual—start the day on the water\, then wander into town and keep the good vibes going. \nEverything is included: stable board\, paddle\, PFD\, and guidance from The Floathouse crew. \nCost: $30 per person (60–90 minutes on the water)\nSUP-PER Club Members: included as part of membership. Ask us how to join! \nNo muss\, no fuss—just good old-fashioned outdoor fun on the river.
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/sunday-funday-sup-paddle-on-the-petaluma-river/
LOCATION:The Floathouse Petaluma\, 50 Water Street\, Petaluma\, CA
CATEGORIES:Recreation
GEO:38.23441;-122.63978
X-APPLE-STRUCTURED-LOCATION;VALUE=URI;X-ADDRESS=The Floathouse Petaluma 50 Water Street Petaluma CA;X-APPLE-RADIUS=500;X-TITLE=50 Water Street:geo:-122.63978,38.23441
END:VEVENT
