SUMMARY:The Bluebyrds at Brewsters
DESCRIPTION:The Bluebyrds play tribute not to just a single artist or band but an entire music genre. \nFolk/rock provided a good bit of the soundtrack of the lives of children of the 60’s and even their children. The Bluebyrds reprise the jangle and harmony of the icons\, such as Buffalo Springfield\, The Byrds\, Bob Dylan\, The Lovin’ Spoonful\, and The Beau Brummels\, just to name a few. You know the songs well and it’s unlikely you’ll be able to resist singing along. The line-up includes seasoned Sonoma County folk/rockers: \n\nLinda Hutchinson: Bass & Vocals\nRick Minervini: Drums \nSteven Nank: Acoustic & Electric Guitars\, Harmonica & Vocals \nTom Richardson: Acoustic & Electric 6 & 12 string Guitars & Vocals  
URL:https://golocal.coop/event/the-bluebyrds-at-brewsters/
LOCATION:Brewsters Beer Garden\, 229 Water Street\, Petaluma\, CA
CATEGORIES:Music
GEO:38.2366;-122.641
